// You have an R×C grid. '.' = free, '#' = wall.
// Moving to a free cell costs 0. You can break ONE wall for cost 1.
// Find minimum cost path from (0,0) to (R-1,C-1).
// Input: R C, then R rows
// Output: minimum cost
// Example:
// 3 3
// .##
// ..#
// .##
// Output: 1

